Which of the following best describes the relationship between pods and containers withKubernetes?
A)  Pods and containers are the same.
B)  Pods can contain multiple containers.
C)  Containers can contain multiple pods.
D)  There is no relationship between pods and containers.
B
B. Pods can contain multiple containers in Kubernetes and this facilitates a shared resourceuse case, where containers can share resources within a pod. When two containers worktogether within a pod, it is sometimes referred to as a sidecar configuration or a sidecarcontainer.Chapter 3: Scripting, Containers, and Automation (Domain 3.0)221
